timeline.bodyText:
This code is specific to the JSON importer, but it was added to a general purpose importing class. This is a problem: writing importers should not require making changes to generic classes like this.
Instead, we should have a generic way to report parsing exceptions to the user. So I propose we do this:

Catch the JsonParseException in the JSON importer;
Extract the message as you are doing here;
Store this message in a new exception, that we could introduce in this PR but could then be reused by other importers (we could call it ImportingParserException);
Then we can still have your isImportingParserException logic with "core-views/check-format" as message that we concatenate.

